olive oil
1 carrot
1 leek
1 packet beef & pork mince
1 packet garlic paste
1 sachet barbecue seasoning
1 packet tomato paste
1 bag baby kale
⅓ cup water
1 packet Shredded Cheddar Cheese
20 g butter
1 sachet mixed sesame seeds
1 packet diced bacon

• Preheat oven to 220°C/200°C fan-forced.
• Grate the carrot. Thinly slice leek.

Little cooks: Under adult supervision, older kids can help grate the carrot.

• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over medium-high heat. Cook diced bacon and beef & pork mince, breaking up with a spoon, until just browned, 3-4 minutes.
• Add carrot and leek and cook until tender, 2-3 minutes.
• Add garlic paste, barbecue seasoning and tomato paste and cook until fragrant, 1 minute.
• Add baby kale and the water, then stir until the kale is wilted, 1-2 minutes. Season to taste.

TIP: Add a splash more water if the filling looks too thick.

• Transfer beef-pork filling to a baking dish and evenly sprinkle with shredded Cheddar cheese.
• In a small heatproof bowl, add the butter and microwave in 10 second bursts until melted.
• Lightly scrunch each sheet of filo pastry and place on top of filling to completely cover.
• Gently brush melted butter over to coat and sprinkle over mixed sesame seeds. Bake pie until golden, 15-20 minutes.

• Divide BBQ beef, pork and bacon filo pie with Cheddar cheese between bowls. Enjoy!